Experiment 10: Build Pipeline using Azure DevOps and Maven

1. Fork the GitHub repository
   Go to GitHub and fork this repository:
   [https://github.com/mvsanthi123/maventestazure](https://github.com/mvsanthi123/maventestazure)

2. Open Azure DevOps
   Go to [https://dev.azure.com](https://dev.azure.com) and log in with your account

3. Create Organization
   Click on “New Organization”
   Enter organization name
   Click Continue

4. Create Project
   Click on “New Project”
   Enter project name (exp10)
   Select visibility as Private
   Click Create

5. Create Pipeline
   Click on Pipelines
   Click on Create Pipeline

6. Connect GitHub
   Select GitHub
   Authorize your GitHub account
   Select the forked repository (maventestazure)

7. Configure Pipeline
   Choose Starter Pipeline or YAML option
   Replace the existing code with the following YAML:

trigger:
branches:
include:
- main

stages:

* stage: __default
  jobs:

  * job: Job
    pool:
    vmImage: ubuntu-latest
    steps:

    * task: Maven@3
      inputs:
      mavenPomFile: 'artifact1/pom.xml'
      mavenOptions: '-Xmx3072m'
      javaHomeOption: 'JDKVersion'
      jdkVersionOption: '17'
      jdkArchitectureOption: 'x64'
      publishJUnitResults: true
      testResultsFiles: '**/surefire-reports/TEST-*.xml'
      goals: 'clean package'

    * task: PublishBuildArtifacts@1
      inputs:
      PathtoPublish: 'artifact1/target'
      ArtifactName: 'drop'
      publishLocation: 'Container'

8. Save and Run
   Click on Save and Run
   Select “Commit directly to main branch”
   Click Run

9. Pipeline Execution
   The pipeline will start automatically
   It will perform the following:

* Fetch code from GitHub
* Run Maven build
* Execute tests
* Generate artifact

10. View Results
    Check pipeline status
    Ensure the following:

* Build successful
* Tests passed
* Artifact generated

11. View Artifact
    Click on Artifacts (drop)
    Download or view the generated files

